By coexistence, does he mean our chemical reactions with the top six?

00:15:33.639 --> 00:15:34.959
There's also assertion.

00:15:34.959 --> 00:15:37.959
Like, maybe I shouldn't get overshadowed by them.

00:15:37.959 --> 00:15:39.559
That could be it.

00:15:39.559 --> 00:15:43.759
I've gotta figure out the point of the assignment and show results in just one game.

00:15:43.759 --> 00:15:45.759
Selection is going to be next to impossible.

00:15:45.759 --> 00:15:47.159
Why can't we hear you?

00:15:47.159 --> 00:15:48.759
Get a straight answer around here!

00:15:48.759 --> 00:15:50.360
Would you shut up?

00:15:50.360 --> 00:15:52.360
Stop doubting yourself.

00:15:52.360 --> 00:15:53.959
It's so lame.

00:15:53.959 --> 00:15:55.959
Have you decided, Bato?

00:15:55.959 --> 00:15:59.159
Anywhere but Team C with Mr. Hassle.

00:15:59.159 --> 00:16:02.159
Playing alongside a familiar face won't help me to grow.

00:16:02.159 --> 00:16:06.559
Wherever I do end up, I just need to rank myself the king like always.

00:16:06.559 --> 00:16:08.360
Pretty simple stuff.

00:16:08.360 --> 00:16:09.959
Damn, I should have known.

00:16:09.959 --> 00:16:11.759
That's 100% you.

00:16:11.759 --> 00:16:13.159
Who else would I be?

00:16:13.159 --> 00:16:15.959
Anyway, why didn't you land in the top six?

00:16:15.959 --> 00:16:16.959
Huh?

00:16:16.959 --> 00:16:19.559
It pisses me off.

00:16:19.559 --> 00:16:22.759
Out of everyone here, you're the guy I wanted to defeat the most.

00:16:22.759 --> 00:16:25.559
So try not to get yourself buried by this place.

00:16:25.559 --> 00:16:27.559
Got it, Donkey?

00:16:27.559 --> 00:16:28.759
Yeah.

00:16:28.759 --> 00:16:29.959
Sorry.

00:16:33.159 --> 00:16:37.159
Isagi, buddy, I'm going to borrow your acne face wash.

00:16:37.159 --> 00:16:39.360
Oh, Nico.

00:16:39.360 --> 00:16:43.360
So it looks like you're having a little trouble picking out a team.

00:16:43.360 --> 00:16:46.559
Yeah, kinda.

00:16:46.559 --> 00:16:49.959
Ego's trying to fan our competitive fire like usual.

00:16:49.959 --> 00:16:51.360
But at the end of the day,

00:16:51.360 --> 00:16:54.959
I think we're being tested on whether we can gel with the top six.

00:16:54.959 --> 00:16:56.759
Gel with them, huh?

00:16:56.759 --> 00:16:59.159
Have you decided?

00:16:59.360 --> 00:17:03.559
My choice is whoever allows me to stick to playing my own style.

00:17:03.559 --> 00:17:06.960
I'm tired of always being cast as the foil.

00:17:06.960 --> 00:17:08.960
No one's going to give you the lead role.

00:17:08.960 --> 00:17:12.559
You taught me you have to steal it.

00:17:12.559 --> 00:17:14.359
Maybe that's the answer.

00:17:14.359 --> 00:17:16.960
A team where I can be the lead.

00:17:20.960 --> 00:17:23.359
Now that I've said my piece,

00:17:23.359 --> 00:17:25.359
do you mind getting out already?

00:17:25.359 --> 00:17:26.759
I'm washing my forehead.

00:17:26.759 --> 00:17:27.960
I don't want you watching.

00:17:27.960 --> 00:17:28.559
Leave.

00:17:28.559 --> 00:17:30.359
Sorry, I was done anyway.

00:17:30.359 --> 00:17:32.359
Why would that embarrass him?

00:17:38.960 --> 00:17:42.960
It won't be easy showing my worth on a team with Rin on it.

00:17:42.960 --> 00:17:48.759
There's a possibility I'll get buried without being able to prove anything.

00:17:48.759 --> 00:17:53.559
Which means the person I should team up with is…

00:17:53.559 --> 00:17:55.960
It's not an easy choice, is it?

00:17:55.960 --> 00:17:58.159
Neo.

00:17:58.160 --> 00:18:00.759
I'm in the same boat as you.

00:18:00.759 --> 00:18:04.160
Figured you would've instantly picked Nagi's group.

00:18:04.160 --> 00:18:08.560
That's Rich coming from the guy who drove us apart in the first place.

00:18:08.560 --> 00:18:10.759
My bad.

00:18:10.759 --> 00:18:12.960
He was the original plan,

00:18:12.960 --> 00:18:15.560
but these days I'm not so sure.

00:18:15.560 --> 00:18:17.360
Why is that?

00:18:17.360 --> 00:18:19.360
Really?

00:18:19.360 --> 00:18:23.360
I mean, he chose you over me during the second selection.

00:18:23.360 --> 00:18:26.160
My desire to get back at him brought me this far.

00:18:26.160 --> 00:18:27.160
Sure.

00:18:29.160 --> 00:18:33.160
But watching him make his way into the top six

00:18:33.160 --> 00:18:37.160
and comparing our current levels of play…

00:18:37.160 --> 00:18:41.160
It feels like he keeps moving further ahead out of my reach.

00:18:41.160 --> 00:18:46.160
I don't have the confidence to play alongside him now.

00:18:46.160 --> 00:18:51.160
If I pass up this opportunity, I might not get a second chance.

00:18:51.160 --> 00:18:54.160
If I show I'm weaker than him though,

00:18:54.160 --> 00:18:58.160
something tells me he's going to slip away entirely.

00:19:00.759 --> 00:19:04.160
The truth is I don't know what to do.

00:19:05.960 --> 00:19:08.960
I'm the same, Rio.

00:19:08.960 --> 00:19:10.560
You know here, right?

00:19:10.560 --> 00:19:12.360
If we don't play together now,

00:19:12.360 --> 00:19:17.759
there's a chance he'll go to a place where I can never reach him.

00:19:17.759 --> 00:19:21.160
And that is one regret that I don't want to have.

00:19:21.160 --> 00:19:23.560
Alright. Thanks a lot.

00:19:23.559 --> 00:19:25.759
Because of our talk, I've decided.

00:19:25.759 --> 00:19:29.559
You know, I bet it's not actually about what the right answer is.

00:19:29.559 --> 00:19:34.159
What matters is having the resolve to turn your decision into the right answer.

00:19:35.559 --> 00:19:36.759
I'll do it.

00:19:36.759 --> 00:19:39.359
I'm going to prove the path I've chosen wasn't a mistake,

00:19:39.359 --> 00:19:40.960
and that I'm right.

00:19:43.759 --> 00:19:46.159
The selection deadline has closed.

00:19:46.159 --> 00:19:48.759
The last assignment will begin shortly.

00:19:48.759 --> 00:19:52.960
After changing into your kits, report to the hall immediately.

00:19:54.559 --> 00:19:56.359
The results have been tallied.

00:19:56.359 --> 00:19:59.559
We will now present the team divisions.

00:19:59.559 --> 00:20:01.359
So it begins.

00:20:01.359 --> 00:20:05.159
My final assignment before the match against Japan's U20s.

00:20:05.159 --> 00:20:09.159
The tryouts to determine who will be on the Blue Lock 11.

00:20:09.159 --> 00:20:11.359
The team I chose was...

00:20:11.359 --> 00:20:17.159
And the person I want to be standing alongside most is you, Rin.

00:20:19.559 --> 00:20:21.960
Bachira wants to be on Team A.

00:20:21.960 --> 00:20:23.559
The same as me.

00:20:25.160 --> 00:20:29.160
Baro, Raichi, Niko, and Chiguri.

00:20:29.160 --> 00:20:30.559
What a lineup.

00:20:31.360 --> 00:20:34.559
Zantetsu and Kagamaru are in Nagi's group?

00:20:35.360 --> 00:20:37.160
But Ayo's in C, too.

00:20:37.960 --> 00:20:42.759
So despite your doubts, you still chose to play alongside him.

00:20:42.759 --> 00:20:44.160
Be irreplaceable.

00:20:44.160 --> 00:20:47.960
The key to acing the tryouts is assertion and coexistence.

00:20:47.960 --> 00:20:50.360
I have to make a case for myself.

00:20:51.160 --> 00:20:54.759
And show them that my presence here can get us wins.

00:20:55.559 --> 00:21:00.160
And after this battle's done, it's on to Japan's U20s.

00:21:05.360 --> 00:21:07.160
Well, Hoi-chan.

00:21:08.360 --> 00:21:10.759
I hope everything is crystal clear.

00:21:10.759 --> 00:21:12.360
Yes, sir.

00:21:12.960 --> 00:21:15.759
Anything for the sake of Japanese soccer.

00:21:15.759 --> 00:21:18.559
Anything for the sake of Japanese soccer.

00:21:23.759 --> 00:21:25.160
Crush them!

00:21:25.160 --> 00:21:25.759
Yes!

00:21:25.759 --> 00:21:27.359
Demolish those fools!

00:21:27.359 --> 00:21:31.960
A bunch of unhinged, nobody's thinking they can rep Japanese soccer!

00:21:31.960 --> 00:21:33.960
Please don't worry, sir.

00:21:33.960 --> 00:21:36.160
We're dealing with idealists here.

00:21:36.160 --> 00:21:41.759
The notion that Japan's U20s could be anyone but who we say is pure insanity.

00:21:45.759 --> 00:21:52.160
Right. There's our little J.F.U. loyalist, deaf to all except us, Hoi-Chi the Earless.

00:21:52.160 --> 00:21:55.759
You know I'm sensitive about the moniker the Internet's given me.

00:21:58.359 --> 00:22:02.359
You've heard everything. I'll be counting on you, Captain.

00:22:02.359 --> 00:22:05.359
Yeah, sure. I accept your offer.

00:22:06.559 --> 00:22:08.359
Let's go, Blue Lock.

00:22:09.960 --> 00:22:11.359
We'll win!

00:22:11.759 --> 00:22:13.960
And I'll prove what I already know.

00:22:13.960 --> 00:22:16.960
I'm going to be the number one striker in the world.

00:22:16.960 --> 00:22:18.160
The best!

00:23:43.960 --> 00:23:48.960
Blue Lock

00:23:49.759 --> 00:23:52.160
Blue Lock. Additional time.

00:23:56.960 --> 00:24:00.360
Start preparing for the tryouts by top six.

00:24:01.960 --> 00:24:03.360
Uh, wait.

00:24:03.360 --> 00:24:05.559
We're divided into triple rooms?

00:24:05.559 --> 00:24:08.160
Looks like we gotta decide on groups.

00:24:08.160 --> 00:24:09.360
Who's first?

00:24:09.759 --> 00:24:12.160
I'm taking one room for myself.

00:24:12.160 --> 00:24:13.759
You five can share the other.

00:24:13.960 --> 00:24:15.160
What the hell?

00:24:15.160 --> 00:24:17.360
No way. Not happening.

00:24:18.160 --> 00:24:20.759
We just need to split into two groups.

00:24:20.759 --> 00:24:22.559
How about Team Rock and Team Paper?

00:24:23.160 --> 00:24:25.559
Yeah, no. There's nothing exciting about that.

00:24:25.559 --> 00:24:28.559
How about Rock, Paper, Scissors? Loser sleeps outside.

00:24:28.559 --> 00:24:29.960
Now that I like.

00:24:29.960 --> 00:24:31.960
It's ego, Rock, Paper, Scissors.

00:24:32.559 --> 00:24:34.559
Huh? You turned it into a hassle.

00:24:34.559 --> 00:24:36.559
Hell yeah, man! Let's do this!

00:24:36.559 --> 00:24:37.160
Yo.

00:24:37.160 --> 00:24:38.559
I'm gonna make you sleep in the hallway.

00:24:38.559 --> 00:24:39.160
Hello?

00:24:39.160 --> 00:24:40.360
Rock, Paper, Scissors!

00:24:40.360 --> 00:24:41.160
Show me now.

00:24:41.160 --> 00:24:42.960
Rock, Paper, Scissors!

00:24:43.559 --> 00:24:44.960
How about we do this?

00:24:44.960 --> 00:24:47.759
Everyone points to the person they least want to be around.

00:24:47.759 --> 00:24:50.960
Afterwards, we divvy up rooms based on results. Cool?

00:24:51.759 --> 00:24:53.360
Sure. That works.

00:24:53.559 --> 00:24:55.360
Okay. Ready?

00:24:55.360 --> 00:24:57.360
Then I choose...

00:25:02.559 --> 00:25:04.960
Meaning I get a room all to myself.

00:25:04.960 --> 00:25:08.160
Uh, no. Scratch that. Let's change that rule.

00:25:09.759 --> 00:25:12.559
Look, I've got no problem sharing a room with this guy.

00:25:12.559 --> 00:25:15.159
And Nagi, we should talk strategy.

00:25:15.159 --> 00:25:16.960
So why don't you join us?

00:25:16.960 --> 00:25:19.359
Oh. Guess that's fine.

00:25:19.759 --> 00:25:22.159
I don't want this to become a bigger hassle.

00:25:22.159 --> 00:25:23.960
Okay, I'll bunk with you.

00:25:24.960 --> 00:25:26.559
You too, monster.

00:25:27.759 --> 00:25:28.759
Whatever.

00:25:33.960 --> 00:25:36.159
Looks like we're rooming together, Spikehead.

00:25:36.159 --> 00:25:37.559
Go look in a mirror.

00:25:37.559 --> 00:25:39.559
Guys, look. I've got spikes too.

